  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>On your turn, as part of the same action used to cast a Bukijutsu, you can enhance your combat output.</p><p> When you deal damage to the target as the result of a Bukijutsu you cast, you deal additional damage based on the type of Bukijutsu cast; </p><p>• If the Bukijutsu makes no more than 2 attacks or forces a saving throw to exactly one creature the first time it deals damage, it deals bonus damage equal to +4 Flurry Die.<br /> This increases to +5 Flurry die at 11th level.</p><p> • If the Bukijutsu makes 3 or more attacks or forces a saving throw to more than one creature, its bonus damage is equal to +1 Flurry Die.<br /> This increases to +2 Flurry die at 11th level.<br /> If the Bukijutsu makes attack rolls, the bonus damage is applied to each successful attack, up to three times.</p><p></p>",
